Task 3: Use Metasploit to Verify Lab Connectivity
Subtask 3.1: Install and Configure Metasploit Framework
Install Metasploit Framework on the host system:

# Install Metasploit dependencies
sudo apt install -y curl wget gnupg2 software-properties-common

# Download and install Metasploit
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rapid7/metasploit-omnibus/master/config/templates/metasploit-framework-wrappers/msfupdate.erb > msfinstall
chmod 755 msfinstall
sudo ./msfinstall

# Initialize Metasploit database
sudo msfdb init

# Start PostgreSQL service
sudo systemctl start postgresql
sudo systemctl enable postgresql
Subtask 3.2: Create Metasploit Testing Scripts
Create scripts to test lab connectivity using Metasploit:

# Create Metasploit connectivity test script
cat > ~/pentest-lab/scripts/metasploit-connectivity-test.rb << 'EOF'
#!/usr/bin/env ruby

# Metasploit connectivity test script
require 'msf/core'

framework = Msf::Simple::Framework.create

# Test 1: Port scanner module
puts "=== Testing Metasploit Connectivity ==="
puts "Running port scanner against pfSense..."

scanner = framework.modules.create('auxiliary/scanner/portscan/tcp')
scanner.datastore['RHOSTS'] = '192.168.100.1'
scanner.datastore['PORTS'] = '22,80,443'

scanner.run_simple(
  'LocalInput' => Rex::Ui::Text::Input::Stdio.new,
  'LocalOutput' => Rex::Ui::Text::Output::Stdio.new
)

puts "Connectivity test completed."
EOF

# Create Metasploit console script
cat > ~/pentest-lab/scripts/msfconsole-test.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash

echo "=== Metasploit Framework Connectivity Test ==="
echo "Starting Metasploit console with automated commands..."

# Create resource script for automated testing
cat > /tmp/msf-test.rc << 'MSFEOF'
use auxiliary/scanner/portscan/tcp
set RHOSTS 192.168.100.1
set PORTS 22,80,443,8080
run

use auxiliary/scanner/http/http_version
set RHOSTS 192.168.100.1
run

exit
MSFEOF

# Run Metasploit with resource script
msfconsole -r /tmp/msf-test.rc

echo "Metasploit connectivity test completed."
EOF

chmod +x ~/pentest-lab/scripts/msfconsole-test.sh
Subtask 3.3: Verify Lab Connectivity
Create a comprehensive connectivity verification script:

# Create comprehensive lab verification script
cat > ~/pentest-lab/scripts/verify-lab-connectivity.sh << 'EOF'
#!/bin/bash

echo "=== Comprehensive Lab Connectivity Verification ==="
echo "Testing Date: $(date)"
echo ""

# Test 1: Network connectivity
echo "1. Testing basic network connectivity..."
ping -c 3 192.168.100.1 > /dev/null 2>&1
if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
    echo "   ✓ pfSense firewall is reachable"
else
    echo "   ✗ pfSense firewall is not reachable"
fi

# Test 2: Port accessibility
echo ""
echo "2. Testing port accessibility..."
nc -zv 192.168.100.1 80 2>/dev/null
if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
    echo "   ✓ HTTP port (80) is accessible"
else
    echo "   ✗ HTTP port (80) is not accessible"
fi

nc -zv 192.168.100.1 443 2>/dev/null
if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
    echo "   ✓ HTTPS port (443) is accessible"
else
    echo "   ✗ HTTPS port (443) is not accessible"
fi

# Test 3: Nmap scan
echo ""
echo "3. Running Nmap scan..."
nmap -sS -p 22,80,443 192.168.100.1 | grep -E "(open|closed|filtered)"

# Test 4: Web interface accessibility
echo ""
echo "4. Testing web interface..."
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://192.168.100.1 > /tmp/http_status
HTTP_STATUS=$(cat /tmp/http_status)
if [ "$HTTP_STATUS" = "200" ] || [ "$HTTP_STATUS" = "302" ]; then
    echo "   ✓ pfSense web interface is accessible (HTTP Status: $HTTP_STATUS)"
else
    echo "   ✗ pfSense web interface is not accessible (HTTP Status: $HTTP_STATUS)"
fi

# Test 5: Metasploit database connectivity
echo ""
echo "5. Testing Metasploit database..."
msfdb status | grep -q "active"
if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then
    echo "   ✓ Metasploit database is active"
else
    echo "   ✗ Metasploit database is not active"
fi

echo ""
echo "=== Lab Connectivity Verification Complete ==="
echo "Results saved to ~/pentest-lab/results/connectivity-test-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S).log"
EOF

chmod +x ~/pentest-lab/scripts/verify-lab-connectivity.sh

# Run the verification script
~/pentest-lab/scripts/verify-lab-connectivity.sh | tee ~/pentest-lab/results/connectivity-test-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S).log
