Troubleshooting Tips
Common Issues and Solutions
Issue 1: pfSense VM fails to start

# Check virtualization support
egrep -c '(vmx|svm)' /proc/cpuinfo

# Ensure KVM modules are loaded
sudo modprobe kvm
sudo modprobe kvm_intel  # For Intel processors
# OR
sudo modprobe kvm_amd    # For AMD processors
Issue 2: Network connectivity problems

# Check virtual network status
virsh net-list --all

# Restart default network
virsh net-destroy default
virsh net-start default

# Check bridge configuration
brctl show
Issue 3: Metasploit database connection issues

# Reinitialize Metasploit database
sudo msfdb delete
sudo msfdb init

# Check PostgreSQL status
sudo systemctl status postgresql
Issue 4: Permission denied errors

# Add user to necessary groups
sudo usermod -a -G libvirt,kvm $USER

# Logout and login again for group changes to take effect
